) The least squares estimators of 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{0}$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{Y\vert x}=\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}x$
\end_inset

 is normally distributed with means 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{1}$
\end_inset

 and variances 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma_{B_{0}}^{2}=\dfrac{{\displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}^{2}}}{{\displaystyle n\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_{i}-\bar{x})^{2}}}\sigma^{2}
\]

\end_inset

 i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{0}\sim\mathcal{N}(\beta_{0},\sigma_{B_{0}})$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

