\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Notation 1.
 
\series default

\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "Notation 1"

\end_inset

The symbols 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{xx},S_{yy},$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{xy}$
\end_inset

 are defined as follows, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
S_{xx} & =\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_{i}-\bar{x})^{2}\quad;\quad S_{yy}=\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_{i}-\bar{y})^{2}\quad;\quad\text{and}\quad S_{xy}=\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_{i}-\bar{x})(y_{i}-\bar{y})
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark
From 
\series bold

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand labelonly
reference "Notation 1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset


\series default
, then the least squares estimators of 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{1}$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{Y\vert x}=\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}x$
\end_inset

 may be written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{\beta}_{1}=\frac{S_{xy}}{S_{xx}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark
Again, from 
\series bold

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand labelonly
reference "Notation 1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{B_{1}}^{2}$
\end_inset

 
\series default
and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{B_{0}}^{2}$
\end_inset

 from 
\series bold
Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:prop9"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 
\series default
and 
\series bold
Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:prop8"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset


\series default
, respectively, can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma_{B_{1}}^{2}=\frac{\sigma^{2}}{S_{xx}}\quad\textit{and}\quad\sigma_{B_{0}}^{2}=\frac{\sigma^{2}}{nS_{xx}}\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "thm:An-unbiased-estimate"

\end_inset

An unbiased estimate of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s^{2}=\frac{\textit{SSE}}{n-2}=\dfrac{{\displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_{i}-\bar{y})^{2}}}{n-2}=\frac{S_{yy}-\hat{\beta}_{1}S_{xy}}{n-2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark
The important parameters 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}$
\end_inset

, estimated by 
\begin_inset Formula $s^{2}$
\end_inset


\series bold
 
\series default
in 
\series bold
Theorem 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:An-unbiased-estimate"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 
\series default
is called a 
\emph on
mean squared error
\emph default
, depicting a type of mean (division by 
\begin_inset Formula $n-2$
\end_inset

) of the squared residuals.

\series bold
 
\end_layout

